<font color="#FF0000">VIETNAM</font><br>
<tt>Fri Feb 21 20:03:12 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
To Art:<br>
     I have read all you said and I really can guess how you feel and have felt, brother-vet, I've felt similiar for awhile.  I wish you a true &quot;Welcome Home&quot;, not in the sense of your just arriving back, but in a sense of your road to dealing with the pain.  In regards to those medals, wear them, put them on the wall, put those stickers in that car window.  Do it for you, and if that's too painful now, do it for our brothers who are not here anymore and never grew old like us.  If anyone asks or wonders, tell them what the were for, the unity and brotherhood among all us that served.  Art, we are part of an exclusive club.  We were are only 9% of our generation, only 2.6 million of us served and that club isn't getting any bigger.  If this country didn't thank you right (it didn't) let the thanks be from a brother vet. Thanks for being there with us!  I wish you all the best.  To all the others out there, if you need to get something off your chest, do it, let the chips fall where they may. God Bless All.
<p><code>--   (Pointman) </code><p>


